# Trivy vulnerability ignore file
# Format: one CVE-ID or GHSA-ID per line, optionally followed by an expiry date
# Example:
#   CVE-2023-12345
#   GHSA-xxxx-yyyy-zzzz until:2026-06-01
#
# Add entries here for accepted risks or vulnerabilities with no available fix
# when ignore-unfixed: true in the workflow does not cover them.

# ncurses 6.5+20250216-2 (Debian 13 Trixie): stack-based buffer overflow in
# infocmp's analyze_string function. No fix available in Debian 13 yet.
# Applies to libncursesw6, libtinfo6, ncurses-base, ncurses-bin.
# Revisit at expiry; remove once Debian ships a patched ncurses package.
CVE-2025-69720 until:2027-01-01

# systemd 257.9-1~deb13u1 (Debian 13 Trixie): arbitrary code execution or
# Denial of Service via spurious IPC messages. No fix available in Debian 13
# yet. Applies to libsystemd0 and libudev1.
# Revisit at expiry; remove once Debian ships a patched systemd package.
CVE-2026-29111 until:2027-01-01

# zlib1g 1:1.3.dfsg+really1.3.1-1+b1 (Debian 13 Trixie): infinite loop in
# CRC32 combine functions leads to Denial of Service. NVD CVSS 5.5 (MEDIUM),
# no fix available in Debian 13 yet. Applies to zlib1g.
# Revisit at expiry; remove once Debian ships a patched zlib package.
CVE-2026-27171 until:2027-01-01
